channel.title: Portforward help
channel.description:
Ok so i want to portforward with a netgear DG834GSP and its not in portforward.com . im not exactly sure what to do or use.
First is this right on portforwarding for 43594 port ? [IMG]http://i19.tinypic.com/6sk386d.jpg[/img]
And now which ip do i use knowing that i have 3 computers using this router? [IMG]http://i7.tinypic.com/6y3y55d.jpg[/img]
And do i need to restart my router after applying the service?
Also whoever helps me i will R3P you.

item.title: Portforward help
item.dc:creator: @bug bug
item.description:
@bug wrote:

yes to the first, go into start menu, then “run…” type “ipconfig/all” might need to space after the ipconfig should see something saying “ip address” use that one. i dont believe u need to restart it but it wouldnt hurt ^^, hope this helped
